Structural verdict:
  No proof-quality monovariant was found.
  The single-vertex candidate fails because vertex 3 can be captured by certified safe first moves under tighter bounds.
  The total-star candidate decreases on the sampled transitions, but total-live-phi and edge-debt increase on many sampled transitions, so these candidates do not give a structural separator from K5-safe states.
  The dominant obstruction after the first few safe captures shifts from vertex deletion to deletion of large low-prime pair edges, so a proof would need a lexicographic invariant controlling both star losses and edge-deletion debt.
